# Progression & Upgrades

## Reputation & Money
* [cite_start]**Reputation:** A single number that increases with wins and decreases with busts; used to unlock new story beats and races[cite: 61].
* [cite_start]**Money:** Earned through racing; spent on upgrades, new cars, and fines[cite: 61].

## The Garage
[cite_start]Players can own between 2 to 5 original car designs[cite: 62]. [cite_start]You begin with a basic "beater" and eventually unlock your father's legendary car as an endgame heirloom[cite: 63].

## Upgrade Tiers
[cite_start]Upgrades are divided into discrete tiers (Lv1 to Lv3)[cite: 64, 65]:
* [cite_start]**Engine:** Improves Acceleration and Top Speed[cite: 65].
* [cite_start]**Tires:** Improves Handling[cite: 65].
* [cite_start]**Nitro:** Increases the duration of the speed burst (activated with SPACE)[cite: 65, 66].
